.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_PlayerClimb
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Player Climb allows player movement based on grabbing of VRTK_InteractableObject objects that have a Climbable grab attach script. Because it works by grabbing, each controller should have a VRTK_InteractGrab and VRTK_InteractTouch component attached.
.NET Framework 3.5.example: VRTK/Examples/037_CameraRig_ClimbingFalling shows how to set up a scene with player climbing. There are many different examples showing how the same system can be used in unique ways.
